            "description": "New Horizon Special School provides 'education for children and vocational training and employment for adults who have intellectual disability.' They strive to develop each child's potential in order for the students to lead a 'productive and satisfying life'. By organising various events and activities, they educate and entertain 140 students. Their philosophy; 'We believe that every child whether handicapped or not, has the right to develop to his or her fullest capabilities'.\n\nMy role at the New Horizon Special School was to entertain the students. I did so by setting up a couple of soccer drills and eventually organising a soccer match, including as many students from the school as I could. The trip to the school was made every two weeks, when I would take the lead role in organising the sports program for the afternoon.     \n\nhttp://www.newhorizon-school-gh.com/index.html"
